<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,901,1367]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1301,1327]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks.</emphasis>
The wide distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[624,786,1301,1326]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Hydroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="diramphus">
<emphasis box="[624,786,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">H. diramphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not limited to polluted areas, occurs in polluted and non polluted areas (
<emphasis box="[383,404,1341,1366]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">cf</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bastida-Zavala, J. R." box="[419,666,1341,1367]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="11 - 39" refId="ref33062" refString="Bastida-Zavala, J. R. (1993) Taxonomia y composicion biogeografica de los poliquetos (Annelida: Polychaeta) de la bahia de La Paz, B. C. S., Mexico. Revista de Investigacion Cientifica, 4, 11 - 39." type="journal article" year="1993">Bastida-Zavala 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
